[HONESTY] This verifies Hamilton's 2D surface theorem NUMERICALLY on a
  discrete octahedron (Chow-Luo combinatorial flow). It does NOT prove
  Poincaré — the 3D conjecture was solved by Perelman (2003). Hexa
  stage1 lacks the PDE infrastructure to run full 3D Ricci flow with
  surgery; that is a ~10,000 LOC C++ project (e.g., Regina/SnapPy).
  BT-547 resolution remains 0/1 MISS for a new proof, but this round
  provides NUMERICAL evidence for the 2D Hamilton uniformization.